{
  "doc_id": "7319",
  "text": "It has also been shown that, in patients with type 1 diabetes, as in patients with type 2 diabetes, peripheral and hepatic insulin resistance may be associated with higher IMCL content [CITATION_1] and that these patients have a greater reliance on lipid than on carbohydrate oxidation to maintain energy homeostasis in the resting condition [CITATION_2] , during moderate exercise [CITATION_3] and after strenuous exercise [CITATION_4] .",
